<li id="cite_note-78"><b><a href="#cite_ref-78" title="">^</a></b> Sullivan, Patricia. <a href="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/11/25/AR2006112500783.html" class="external text" title="http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/11/25/AR2006112500783.html" rel="nofollow">Anti-Communist Priest Gheorghe Calciu-Dumitreasa</a>, <i>The Washington Post</i>, November 26, 2006. Page C09. Accessed May 9, 2008.</li>
<li id="cite_note-time-79">^ <a href="#cite_ref-time_79-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-time_79-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Ostling, Richard. <a href="http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,150718,00.html" class="external text" title="http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,150718,00.html" rel="nofollow">"Cross meets Kremlin"</a>, <i>TIME Magazine</i>, June 24, 2001. Accessed April 7, 2008.</li>
<li id="cite_note-80"><b><a href="#cite_ref-80" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.geocities.com/murati_kled/albanians.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.geocities.com/murati_kled/albanians.htm" rel="nofollow">Van Christo. <i>Albania and the Albanians</i>.</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-81"><b><a href="#cite_ref-81" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://litek.ws/k0nsl/detox/anti-humans.htm" class="external free" title="http://litek.ws/k0nsl/detox/anti-humans.htm" rel="nofollow">http://litek.ws/k0nsl/detox/anti-humans.htm</a> Dumitru Bacu, <i>The Anti-Humans. Student Re-Education in Romanian Prisons]</i>, Soldiers of the Cross, <a href="/wiki/Englewood,_Colorado" title="Englewood, Colorado">Englewood, Colorado</a>, 1971. Originally written in Romanian as <i>Piteşti, Centru de Reeducare Studenţească</i>, Madrid, 1963</li>
<li id="cite_note-82"><b><a href="#cite_ref-82" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Adrian_Cioroianu" title="Adrian Cioroianu">Adrian Cioroianu</a>, <i>Pe umerii lui Marx. O introducere în istoria comunismului românesc</i> ("On the Shoulders of Marx. An Incursion into the History of Romanian Communism"), <a href="/wiki/Editura_Curtea_Veche" title="Editura Curtea Veche">Editura Curtea Veche</a>, Bucharest, 2005</li>
</ol>
